Vinpro, the wine industry body says it will stick to its legal actions against the government despite President Cyril Ramaphosa's decision to partially lift a ban on alcohol sales. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Vinpro will continue litigating against the government, despite the unbanning of alcohol sales. The wine industry body wants the government to consult with it before putting a blanket ban on alcohol sales in future. READ: Winemakers taking govt to court "The approach is very much that of ensuring that any major decisions that impact our businesses are taken on a provincial level," says Vinpro's Maryna Calow. Many jobs have been lost in the industry, while some companies across various affected sectors have shut their doors. Meanwhile, President Cyril Ramaphosa, on Monday, announced adjusted Level 3 lockdown restrictions. COVID-19: Additional vaccine doses expected It remains compulsory for every person to wear a mask in a public space and the new curfew hours are from 11pm to 4am. Watch the full interview above for more details on this story.